'''Sipra''' is a [[Rajput]] tribe in the [[Punjab region]] of [[Pakistan]] and [[India]]. Sipra are one of the most educated and well established families among other [[Jat]] casts.
== History ==
The Sipra are a sub-division of the [[Gill (clan)|Gill]]. The tribe has also given its name to the [[Battle of Sobraon|battlefield of Sobraon]]. They are [[Muslim]] and [[Hindus]], many converted to [[Islam]] in the 16th century. They are in Armed Forces, Executives and judiciary. It means 'super race'.<ref>A Glossary of the tribes & castes of Punjab by H. A Rose</ref>
== Location ==
The tribe is chiefly found along the banks of [[Chenab]] and [[Jhelum]] River, in [[Gujrat]], [[Mandi Bhahauddin]], Kharian, [[Gujranwala]], [[Rahim Yar Khan]], [[AhmedPurEast]], [[Sahiwal]], [[Multan]], [[Karachi]], [[Sargodha]] and [[Layyah]] Districts, and are specially numerous in [[Kabirwala]] District [[Khanewal]], [[Jhang District]], Gojra, [[Chiniot District]]. The Sipra have no connection with the surname Sapru, which is, in fact, a [[Kashmiri Pundit]] surname.
